  "doc_id": "51835",
  "text": "Tigecycline is licensed in Italy to treat complicated intra-abdominal and skin and soft tissue infections. Good clinical results for tigecycline have been demonstrated previously: for example, Bassetti et al. [CITATION_1] showed a 76.5% (13/17) success rate for tigecycline in the treatment of complicated skin and soft tissue infections and an 82.8% (72/87) success rate against peritonitis. This clinical success is reflected by high tigecycline susceptibility for most pathogens over the course of the T.E.S.T. study between 2004 and 2011: Gram-negative pathogens showed >94% tigecycline susceptibility while Gram-positives were >98% susceptible in the present report.",
  "correct_citation": {
